posting_body: ['No broker fee', 'September 1st move in date', 'Text Lihi @ 3477484234 w/ address 293 Herkimer', 'large and luxury 2 bedroom / 2 baths!', '- Welcome to Fulton Crossing!', 'A new luxury apartment complex located in Brooklyn’s beautiful Bedford-Stuyvesant.', 'An up-and-coming neighborhood in the heart of New York City’s most charming borough, it boasts tree-lined streets, stunning architecture, enchanting parks, and a diverse yet welcoming atmosphere – all within close proximity to the city’s bustling urban hubs.', 'This luxury Brooklyn apartment building offers large studio, 1 bedroom, 2 bedroom and 3 bedroom apartments in Bed-Stuy that feature unobstructed city views, spacious layouts, and state-of-the-art amenities.', 'If you’re searching for a Bedford-Stuyvesant apartment, Fulton Crossing is ready to welcome you home.', 'Building includes two elevators, a furnished rooftop with grills and amazing Manhattan views, gym, Lounge/Co-working area, kids play room, shared courtyard, laundry rooms and parking.', 'Great location half block away from Kingston & Throop C Local train and 2 blocks away from Nostrand Avenue A Express train.', 'A minute away from grocery stores and the bars/restaurants in Bed-Stuy and Crown Heights.', 'Apartment features modern open-concept designs.', 'Sleek finishes and modern hardware add an contemporary edge, while large French-paned windows perfectly frame beautiful views of Bed-Stuy and of natural light.', 'Kitchen with stainless steel appliances, including dishwasher, and extra space for table/island.', 'Spacious bathrooms, large closet, split AC units, hardwood floors throughout, and video intercom system!']

title: 4 Bedrooms + Office W/ Hardwood-Like Floors, Private Yard
posting_body: ['This is a 4 Bedroom + Office in the Union City area of New Jersey.', 'The Apartment Features Hardwood-Like Floors, Private Yard, Professional Grade Stainless Steel Stove, FIOS, and Tile Backsplash.', 'Pets accepted on approval.', 'NO BROKER FEE FOR IMMEDIATE START', 'Kitchen - Dining Room 15 x 10', 'Living Room 16.5 x 9', 'First Bedroom 13 x 11', 'Second Bedroom 9.5 x 7', 'Third Bedroom 11 x 9', 'Fourth Bedroom 12 x 9', 'Office 12.5 x 4', 'Yard 39.5 x 22', 'Listing ID#7893', 'Orientation in Relation to Other Neighborhoods', 'North of Jersey City & Hoboken', 'South of West New York, North Bergen & Guttenberg', 'East of Secaucus', 'West of Weehawken', 'Near Houses of Worship, Shopping and Local Dining Establishments on Bergenline and New York Aves.', '20 Minutes to Midtown via Public Transit or Car!', 'The soul of the city can be found along Bergenline Avenue, a bustling commercial strip where many of the area s residents come to shop, dine and meet up with old friends.', 'Just across John Fitzgerald Kennedy Boulevard, in North Bergen, another mall offers big-box stores, an LA Fitness gym, a ShopRite and a multiplex movie theater, while the many restaurants of Hoboken and Jersey City are within walking distance or a short cab or jitney ride away.', 'Despite its compact size, Union City boasts a number of parks, three with water features, including Firefighter s Memorial Park on Palisade Avenue, which has an Olympic-size pool.', 'Washington Park, where the city borders Jersey City Heights, has a dog run, tennis and basketball courts and baseball fields.', 'The NJ Transit 123 buses make five stops in Union City, with travel times of between 10 and 30 minutes to the Port Authority in New York.', 'Other options include traveling to Hoboken or Jersey City to catch the PATH train; taking an eight-minute ferry from Weehawken to 39th Street; or taking a seven-minute ferry from Hoboken to Wall Street.', "For travel to Jersey City and New York, many residents rely on the jitney buses that run along several of Union City's north-south arteries."]

posting_body: ['Studio + Alcove', 'This unique alcove studio overlooks our tranquil zen garden and has plenty of closet space!', 'The apartment features floor to ceiling windows, hardwood oak floors, LED track lighting, and solar shades.', 'The kitchen includes GE Profile stainless steel appliances, white Italian glass cabinets, composite stone island with breakfast bar extension, and a garbage disposal in the kitchen sink.', 'A Bosch stack-able washer dryer is also included within the residence for your convenience!', 'Mercedes House, New Yorks most important new residential development is changing the cityscape forever.', 'From Two Trees Management Company and visionary architect Enrique Norten comes a luxury rental complex spiraling 29 stories above the city with unobstructed views of the Hudson River.', 'A modern tower of glass and greenery.', 'The good life is lived here.', 'Bold design.', 'Midtown convenience.', 'Mercedes House is the address for life in style.', 'Residents of Mercedes House just don’t rent a home.', 'With the extraordinary array of available amenities, they embrace a lifestyle: State-of-the-art wellness center and health club with indoor and outdoor swimming pools, two outdoor decks with 3 BRAND NEW BBQ grills and picnic tables, great for entertaining!', 'Green space for sunbathing, bocce courts, yoga, spinning, indoor basketball, boxing room, outdoor putting green, outdoor movie theater, and spa facilities.', 'On-site indoor parking available.', 'In a city that has it all, Mercedes House puts it all within reach.', 'Mercedes House is ideally situated on the western edge of midtown Manhattan, rising above the Hudson River and just across from newly renovated Clinton Park.', 'This is where life, work and play intersect.', 'All that defines New York is within easy reach.', 'International markets and restaurants, mom-and-pop shops, Hudson River Park, world-class entertainment.', 'The heart of the city beats just beyond your door.']

title: HUMONGOUS==HIGH CEILING==GREAT LIGHTING==OAK WOOD FLOORS==TOP FLOOR==
posting_body: ['Luxury building in the Financial District, you walk into this beautifully renovated apartment.', 'Upon immediately entering the large foyer, you will notice the large California-style closet providing an efficient storage solution for the apartment.', 'Adjacent to it is the brand new, large pass-thru gourmet kitchen, equipped with granite counters, custom cabinetry, stainless steel GE appliances (including a dishwasher, refrigerator, stove top, microwave, and ventilation system).Slightly further up is the full bathroom boasting a marble-tile finish and a large vanity mirror.', 'The large living space is an effortless FLEX-2 conversion, very comfortably.', 'With substantial remaining space for a living quarters, you can decide where to situate any accommodating furniture (couch, coffee table, etc).', 'Large over-sized windows on the Eastern exposure flood the hardwood floors with natural light and provide fascinating views of the Brooklyn Bridge, South St Seaport, and surrounding waterscape.', 'Settled on Water St, you are surrounded by an endless amount of options in terms of fine dining, shopping, culture and activities.', 'South St Seaport is across the street from your doorsteps.', '55 Fulton Market is conveniently located one block to the North.', 'Titanic Memorial Park is across the street.', "NYC's historic Financial District and all its attractions are a five minute walk to the South-West.", 'Transit options surround the area, with the primary hub being the newly renovated Fulton Street Station (operational 24 hours a day) where you can catch eight different train lines (including 2, 3, 4, 5, A, C, J, Z).']

posting_body: ['This magnificent 4Bedrooms and 3 bath apartment in Classic pre-war full service building in the heart of the Upper West Side.', 'Size is about 2,400 square feet and has a large entry foyer with a two entry closets.', 'Kitchen will be fully renovated with all brand new with stainless steel appliances, microwave & dishwasher,', 'customized marble countertops, ample storage space, and gorgeous slate tiled floors and white wood cabinetry.', 'Spacious living room with a fireplace, north which provides good natural light and gorgeous city views.', 'Off the living area and through charming French doors is a formal dining room.', 'Well sized bedrooms including a Master bedroom with multiple closets and Primary bath in suite.', 'The fourth bedroom can be used as a guest room, nanny room or home office,  and has an en-suite bathroom.', 'decent closet space and charming hardwood floors throughout the apartment.', 'High ceilings with fine pre-war crown moldings.', 'Spacious pantry off the kitchen with washer & dryer.', 'Close to the subway and just minutes walking from to Central Park.', 'Located between Riverside Park and Central Park, the Upper West Side has gained for providing a laid-back, easygoing lifestyle within NYC.', 'Stunning Art-Deco architecture  help give the area its distinctively sophisticated surrounding']

title: Two-Bedroom Penthouse in Hunters Point
posting_body: ['Stellar Duplex Penthouse Condo with private outdoor space and the best view in Hunters Point!', 'Enjoy luxury living in this beautiful sprawling 2 Bedroom 3 Bath condo with soaring ceilings and a stylish convenient layout.', 'The first level features an expansive living room that is flooded with gorgeous natural light.', 'The living room opens to a tremendous private terrace, well-appointed for quiet contemplation or entertaining in style.', 'The panoramic views will inspire you.', 'This is living well in the greatest city in the world!', 'The modern open kitchen is fit for a budding Paul Bocuse; outfitted with high-end stainless steel appliances and set up nicely with an emphasis on both form and function.', 'With a Viking stove, Italian granite countertops and quality triple lacquered cabinetry, all that is needed is your ingenuity and a few kitchen accoutrements to create the perfect meal to pair with your housewarming party!', 'The bedrooms are on the second floor and each is ideally configured.', 'The spacious primary bedroom has great closet space, along with extra storage.', 'The en-suite bathroom has Italian marble, a double sink, a deep soaking tub and a separate shower.', 'The second bedroom features a private balcony to start the day with some fresh air and that phenomenal view!', 'This bedroom also has an en-suite bathroom.', '*Two bicycle spots are included in the rent, along with access to all of the fabulous amenities!', 'The View at East Coast is a luxury building, designed by Handel Architects, on Gantry Plaza State Park.', 'It is the only waterfront condominium building in Long Island City.', 'This 24-hour doorman building has everything covered.', 'Residents have access to a staggering array of the finest amenities, including an indoor swimming pool, billiards room, fitness center, spa, cinema, yoga room and lounges.', 'Plus, the super fast commute from here to Manhattan or Brooklyn is a breeze.', 'The convenient public transportation options include the NYC Ferry and the E/M/G/7.', 'The building is in close proximity to a range of exceptional restaurants, nightlife and culture.', 'Long Island City has some of the best contemporary art destinations the city has to offer, including MoMA PS1!']

posting_body: ['Sun drenched apartment with STUNNING water and city VIEWS available for rent starting September 1st.', 'This home has an updated galley kitchen with KitchenAid range, dishwasher and Fisher & Paykel refrigerator.', 'The large primary bedroom can come with a king sized murphy bed (or not) and has plenty of room for a full set of furniture plus an office area.', 'The ensuite marble full bath with separate shower/jacuzzi tub will make you feel like you’re at the spa in your own home.', 'The secondary room can be used as a second bedroom or separate office space/guest bedroom.', 'Herringbone wood flooring throughout.', 'The Promenade is a luxury full service gem on the UES!', 'Your apartment comes with access to a pool (can be reserved for private use daily), gym with views (two Pelotons + pilates reformer), sauna, locker rooms, private massage room, 24 hour concierge, doormen, porters, handymen, live-in super, game/playroom, roof top jogging track, business/conference room, large laundry room, dry cleaning services, bicycle room and a large top floor residents lounge.', 'The playroom and lounge can be rented out for private parties.', 'Each have their own kitchen for catering.', 'John Jay park, PS 158 and the East River Promenade are steps away.', 'Central Park, Museum Mile and all the goodness of the UES are knocking at your door.', 'This is a wonderful place to call home!', 'Showings by appointment only.', 'NO BROKER FEE.', 'Cats (max 2) are ok, unfortunately the building will not allow dogs.', '1 or 2 year lease accepted.', 'Reduced rent is available should use of amenities not be necessary.']

posting_body: ['STAINLESS STEEL APPLIANCES / LAUNDRY IN UNIT / CONCIERGE / PARKING / PET FRIENDLY', 'Listing ID #: 211201', 'Price: $15,995', 'Property Type: Apartment', 'Bedrooms: 3.0', 'Bathrooms: 2.5', 'Pets: Pets OK', 'Building Amenities', 'Doorman', 'Elevator', 'Laundry', 'Welcome to your new home!', 'As soon as you walk into this elegant 3 bedroom residence you will be WOWED.', "With it's gracious and generously proportioned rooms, large windows and an abundance of light, it offers the finest of living.", 'You will appreciate the impeccably scaled grand living room, modern kitchen with stainless steel appliances and generous closet space.', 'Bring your interior designer and make this your forever home!', 'Pictures provided show the finishes of a similar apartment.', "Located in one of New York City's most desirable addresses, this elegant and iconic Upper East Side building stands 21-stories tall and features 68 luxury homes.", 'Each residence exhibits large open floor plans ranging from spacious two bedrooms to grand four bedroom homes, all with washer/dryers.', 'This 24-hour doorman buildings prime location gives residents access to some of the best fine dining and luxury shopping New York City has to offer.', 'You also have Museum Mile and Central Park right at your doorstep.', 'One of the most beautiful neighborhoods in the city, the Upper East Side feels a lot like Paris: cosmopolitan, refined, and set apart from the chaos of the rest of the city.', 'Close to many tourist destinations, the UES is always lively, but the historic architecture, clean sidewalks, and manicured flowerbeds give it a calm, unhurried atmosphere.', 'For showings contact:', 'Adel Talebpour / The Bouklis Group / 212-961-7334 (cell) / <URL> / <URL> / <URL>', 'Adel Talebpour', 'Phone: 212-402-7855', 'Mobile: 212-961-7334', 'Email: <URL>', 'The Bouklis Group \xa0 212-402-7855 \xa0 212-961-7334 \xa0 <URL>', 'POSTED BY REALTYMX™', 'To view, call or text Adel Talebpour at 212-961-7334']

posting_body: ['THE COOLEST NO FEE LOFT ON THE MARKET, COME AND GET IT.', 'Internationals are easily accepted.', "Over the course of 8 years, I've lived in 3 apartments in the building.", "It's been amazing to watch this community and neighborhood as a whole grow together.", "FANTASTIC neighborhood if you're unfamiliar, essentials all around.", 'Chase Bank, supermarket, cafes, bodegas at the corner alone.', 'Barons (the restaurant) and Home Depot are just in back of us.', '7 minute walk to Von King Park (dog run / newly renovated lawn / outdoor amphitheater with weekend music).', '10 minute bike ride to Fort Greene Park (local veggies and hand-made textiles weekly!), 15 minute bike ride to Domino Park (right on the water / view of city).', '10 minute bus straight to Downtown Brooklyn (Whole Foods, Target, Apple Store, Atlantic Terminal).', '20 minute bike ride to Prospect Park.', '**', 'The building is 1 block to the subway, VERY EASY TO GET TO MANHATTAN.', 'First come first served, we take one application at a time*', 'The community is absolutely terrific - I love my neighbors, and the management is top notch.', 'The Super is very attentive and lives with his family in the building.', 'The landlord is not only friendly, but a good communicator if any issues arises as well.', 'K041 Lofts has a spectacular unit available come September 5th for a year lease.', 'With soaring 18 ft ceilings, massive windows, and plenty of floor place.', '1 floor walk-up, pets allowed, and amenity building.', 'We have a projector movie theater, stroller parking, car parking, a sunny loft gym, dance studio, pool table wifi lounge, laundry (via app), free bike storage, and two gigantic rooftops with 360 views including the Manhattan skyline!', 'Get creative with that floor space and wall space!', 'Perfect for big rugs, hanging plants, wall decor, film projector, EVEN great height for acrobatics!', 'We have a couple in the building :)', 'There is a king size windowless room-', 'You can utilize this as a bedroom (most do).', "I've seen gorgeous walk-in closets, soundproof music studios, nurseries, etc. Renovated kitchen with island with full size steel appliances including dishwasher, microwave, and gas stove (great for bills).", 'The bathroom is large with stone floors and stone wall.', 'There is a deep tub great for baths.', 'Perfect if you have a pup or a little one too!', 'If you are interested, PLEASE email me right away for the application.', 'Talk soon!', 'It is occupied so let me know time frames that work for you this week.']

title: 2br - $2200 / 2 bd room apt. (yonkers ny)
posting_body: ['While rents are going up everywhere in the NYC metro area, this rent is about 3k less than what you find in the metro area and a great location and safe location as well.', ' No shootings, muggings, assaults in this hood..', 'Safe walk to metro north..', 'By Owner..2 bedroom/1bath apt for rent.', 'fresh paint.', '2nd floor.', '10 min walk to metro north station in woodlawn, 20 min commute to grand central station.', 'Heat and water included.', '$ 2200 per month.', '1st, last, security and references.', 'accommodates 3 personas', 'Huge eat in kitchen, tall ceilings, extra storage areas, wood floors.', 'Street parking', 'TO QUALIFY FOR THIS APARTMENT FOLLOW THE 30% RENT RULE...', 'In simple terms, the 30% rule recommends that your monthly rent payment not be more than 30% of your gross monthly income.', '...', 'That would leave 70% of your gross monthly income to cover other necessities, such as utilities and food, discretionary spending, debt repayment, and savings.', 'Rule of Thumb: How Much Should You Spend on Rent? -', 'The <URL> › ... › Real Estate Resources', 'Search for: 30% rent rule', 'HOW MUCH DO I HAVE TO EARN IN ORDER TO AFFORD  $2200 A MONTH IN RENT..', 'You may have heard of the general rule of thumb here, which is that 30% of your monthly income should go to rent.', "If you make $7800 a month at your job, that's $1950 that you can afford to spend in housing costs.", '(Another way to calculate this is to take your entire yearly income and divide it by 40.)Feb 8, 2019', 'How Much Rent Can You Afford? - <URL> › tips › how-much-rent-can-you...', '2200 a month..its a no brainier..', 'Call business # 10AM -5 PM   # 914 776 9139, lv msg if no one answers.........(THIS MEANS NO E-MAILS!!-BECAUSE YOU WILL BE WASTING YOUR TIME...why you ask?', 'BECAUSE THIS AD IS POSTED AS A SERVICE TO THE OWNER OF THIS PROPERTY.', 'THE PERSON WHO POSTED THIS DOES NOT OWN THE PROPERTY!!!!)']

posting_body: ['This townhouse duplex is an absolute one of a kind stunning fully renovated 2300 sq ft of live, play, wotrk opportunity.', "It consits of a gorgeous sunlit 3-bedroom living quarters and a family play area or home office located in a classic corner limestone building with windows all aroundand and a private backyard located in the best part of Bay Ridge called Doctor's Row.", 'This is an ideal for a family with a home office.', 'Three-bedroom apartment is very spacious and tastefully decorated; multiple antique details from the last two centuries, high ceilings, Andersen doors, Built-in antique furniture, crystal and wall-mounted panel TVs; state-of-the-art bathroom with bath enclosure, powder room with bidet; great kitchen with lots of cabinets, granit countertop, recessed lightes and breakfast nook, kitchen leads to a unique dining room with an entrance to a huge very private backyard.', 'At the lower level, there is another 1100 sq ft harwood floor space which includes: 4+ rooms, restroom, walk-in bath, private street entrance, and access to the private backyard.', 'This space is ideal for someone who started their business from home or needs a quiet space for different family members to study, play, relax, or have their live-in nany close by.', 'Every room has a water connection if needed.', 'You will have access to the backyard from both levels.', 'The entire rent can be written off in tax deductions if the lower level used as an office.', 'Located at a prominent professional Bay Ridge community, in a business oriented area with plenty of restaurants, shopping, banks, medical offices in every building, 2 minutes from the R train subway station and extensive Brooklyn bus routes, five minutes from the X27 and X37 Express buses to Manhattan, and a 10 minute walk to the 69th Street Ferry to Manhattan.', 'Retired medical professionals are offering for rent this wonderful duplex where you will have place for everything: family and entertaining, and start or expand your own business.', 'Central A/C and heater combination extraquiet split system allows for temperature control in every room.', 'Laundry unit is at the lower level.', 'Parking space provides 2 car parking opprtunity.', 'Rent 8,500/month for both office and living quaters.', 'At least 2-year lease.', 'EMAIL to schedule viewing.', 'No pets please.', 'No smoking please.']

title: Room For Rent - Sept 1st
posting_body: ['One bedroom for a SEPTEMBER 1ST move in available in a beautiful 3 bedroom, 1 bathroom apartment right in the heart of Prospect Heights.', 'We live a 10-minute walk from the B/Q/A/C/2/3.', 'The apartment is surrounded by tons of bars & restaurants.', "There is a laundromat right around the corner that's open late and is super convenient.", 'The apartment is also within walking distance to Prospect Park, Brooklyn Botanical Garden, and the Brooklyn Museum.', "It’s an amazing price for the location and we've loved living in this apartment!", 'The room is 7.5’ by 11.5’ with a window, spacious closet and hardwood floors.', 'The room will be unfinished and will be $1000 a month and a security deposit of $1000 for move in.', 'Utilities (gas and electric) are usually between $65-$100 depending on the season.', 'Usually higher in the summer with AC usage.', 'The roommates: 30 year old (f) working in fashion and a 29 year old (f) pilates instructor.', 'We both work quite a bit so we like to have nice homey environment.', 'We are looking for a clean and courteous roommate.', 'We go out occasionally but never bring the party home so we appreciate someone who feels the same way.', 'Just overall looking for someone who will be respectful and a great addition to the apartment!', 'Must be good with dogs - We have a very sweet rescue pit/mix who is wary of strangers at first, but becomes a lap dog once she knows you.', 'We signed a new lease last year after the dog moved in that prohibits pets, but luckily they grandfathered her in and allowed for us to stay.', 'This unfortunately means no other pets are allowed.', 'Thanks!']

title: Beautiful 3 bed/2 bath apartment in prime Red Hook
posting_body: ['PERFECT FOR SHARES:', 'Available immediately, this 3 bed/2 bath apartment is located on a beautiful, quiet street in Red Hook, one of the most active and tight-knit communities in Brooklyn.', 'Sitting on the third floor of a two-family townhouse, this brand new unit features stainless steel kitchen appliances, in-unit washer/dryer, and split A/C and heating units throughout.', 'The primary bedroom has an en-suite bathroom, with windows that overlook Columbia Street and flood the room with light.', 'The two other bedrooms are perfect for an office, nursery, guest room, or an extra room to relax.', 'The kitchen and dining/living area is bright and beautiful, with a skylight that allows sunshine to come in from above.', 'Pull down the ladder in the hallway to access the roof hatch, revealing beautiful city views.', '364 Columbia Street is just a short distance to the award-winning bars and restaurants that make Red Hook one of the most exciting places to live in New York.', "Hometown Barbecue, Widow Jane Distillery, Van Brunt Stillhouse, Red Hook Tavern, Brooklyn Crab, Keg & Lantern, Strong Rope Brewery, Red Hook Lobster Pound, Steve's Key Lime, Sunny's Bar, and so much more are just a stone's throw away.", 'Make your way north along the water to Brooklyn Bridge Park, or journey south to Valentino Pier for the most breathtaking views of the Statue of Liberty accessible by land.', 'Pets permitted.', 'Please email for details or to make an appointment to view.']

posting_body: ['Welcome to Fulton Crossing!', 'A new luxury apartment complex located in Brooklyn’s beautiful Bedford-Stuyvesant.', 'An up-and-coming neighborhood in the heart of New York City’s most charming borough, it boasts tree-lined streets, stunning architecture, enchanting parks, and a diverse yet welcoming atmosphere – all within close proximity to the city’s bustling urban hubs.', 'This luxury Brooklyn apartment building offers large studio, 1 bedroom, 2 bedroom and 3 bedroom apartments in Bed-Stuy that feature unobstructed city views, spacious layouts, and state-of-the-art amenities.', 'If you’re searching for a Bedford-Stuyvesant apartment, Fulton Crossing is ready to welcome you home.', 'Building includes two elevators, a furnished rooftop with grills and amazing Manhattan views, gym, Lounge/Co-working area, kids play room, shared courtyard, laundry rooms and parking.', 'Great location half block away from Kingston & Throop C Local train and 2 blocks away from Nostrand Avenue A Express train.', 'A minute away from grocery stores and the bars/restaurants in Bed-Stuy and Crown Heights.', 'Apartment features modern open-concept designs.', 'Sleek finishes and modern hardware add an contemporary edge, while large French-paned windows perfectly frame beautiful views of Bed-Stuy and of natural light.', 'Kitchen with stainless steel appliances, including dishwasher, and extra space for table/island.', 'Spacious bathrooms, large closet, split AC units, hardwood floors throughout, and video intercom system!', 'Showing by appointment - Text Izzy 917-386-9552']

posting_body: ['Beautiful 2 Bedroom apartment, 1 Block from Silver Lake Park, 3 Blocks from Richmond University Medical Center (RUMC).', '5 Minutes ride to SI Ferry/Empire Outlets, Van Duzer Street and Victory Blvd commercial districts,', '2 Minutes ride to Forest Ave commercial district.', "Staten Island's Northshore offers some of the best parks and most culturally diverse restaurants and neighborhoods outside of Queens, at a fraction of the cost for living and much less crowded.", 'Enjoy the Yard and View of Manhattan and NJ from the living room and Balcony.', 'Beautiful wood floors, high ceilings w/crown moldings, medallions and chandeliers.', 'Washer and electric dryer hookups in basement.', "This early 1900's colonial house is being restored with as much original detail as possible with exterior restoration to follow.", 'Very conveniently located near: Richmond University Medical Center (RUMC), Snug Harbor Cultural Center, Staten Island Botanical Garden, Staten Island Zoo, Richmond University Medical Center, Schools, Silver Lake Park and Golf Course, Goodhue Park, Clove Lakes Park, Staten Island Baseball Stadium, SI Ferry, YMCA and JCC.', 'Heat/Hot Water Included', 'Working professionals', 'Full background/credit checks', 'Agents welcome only with properly vetted clientele', 'Please call (917) 583-2791', '----Espanol/Spanish----', 'Hermoso apartamento de dos habitaciones.', 'Sólo a un bloque del Parque y Campo de Golf de Silver Lake; a cinco minutos en auto del Staten Island Ferry/Empire Outlets, y las áreas comerciales de la calle Van Duzer y el bulevar Victory; y a dos minutos en auto del área comercial de la avenida Forest.', 'La costa norte de Staten Island tiene algunos de los mejores parques y la mayor diversidad cultural de restaurantes y vecindarios después de Queens, a una fracción del costo de vivienda y mucho menos gente.', 'Disfruta de las áreas exteriores, incluyendo el porche (balcón) en la parte delantera (compartido), y la plataforma de madera (deck) y patio en la parte trasera (compartido).', 'El apartamento incluye pisos en madera de roble, puertas de bolsillo y techos altos, todos con hermosos detalles decorativos y originales, además de candelabros y gabinetes de cocina con diseños particulares.', 'También tenemos disponible conexiones', 'para lavadora y secadora en el sótano (basement).', 'El lugar tiene un estilo colonial de principios de los 1900s y está siendo restaurado tomando en cuenta la mayoría de los detalles originales posibles, incluyendo la restauración del exterior en los próximos meses.', 'Convenientemente localizado cerca de los siguientes lugares: Centro Cultural de Snug Harbor; title: Spacious 4BR/3BA Home for Rent
posting_body: ['Beautiful, well-kept 4 bedroom/3 full bathroom split-level home in the sough-after Valhalla school district is available for rent immediately.', 'It’s situated on a wonderful, quiet tree-lined street in one of the best neighborhoods.', 'This spacious home features a large, beautifully landscaped private backyard that includes watershed property at the back, a finished downstairs with kitchenette, fireplace, and separate entrance.', 'The upstairs master bedroom features an attached full bath, and walk-in closet.', 'An eat-in kitchen with granite countertops, a new stainless-steel dishwasher, and a private enclosed back deck that is accessible via the dining room and the kitchen.', 'The downstairs is attractive as an office, a play space, in-law or au-pair suite with lots of storage spaces.', ' Complete with central A/C, 2 zone heat, a fireplace, laundry in the home, 2 car attached garage with additional driveway space, hardwood floors and a bonus room.', 'The home is in the quaint village of Valhalla, with the Metro North Station and Kensico Dam Plaza within walking distance.', 'It’s just a 40 minute ride to Manhattan, and 8 minutes to White Plains.', ' It is also a close distance to shops, schools, town pool, rec.', 'center, and library.']

title: Berkshire home with garage and yard
posting_body: ['Hello, my name is Nick and I’m going to be renting my house in Great Barrington, MA for one year beginning October 1st, 2022 through October 1st, 2023 while I go hiking across the country.', 'A Pied-à-terre perhaps?', 'A Berkshire getaway shared with friends?', 'You decide what you want to call it but there will only be one lease with no more than two lessee’s.', 'Option to renew after one year is available with stipulations and rent increase TBD.', 'I work professionally as a residential home builder and have been refreshing the look and feel of the house since closing in January of 2022.', 'The house is very structurally sound, but like most things from the 1960’s, needs some TLC which I’ve been providing it with.', 'Currently the house is still being worked on, mostly cosmetically in the form of paint, overdue maintenance and light renovations.', 'The house is presently occupied by three tenants who will all be moved out by the end of September, so it’s more than liveable as-is but I’m making it better every day before I leave for my walkabout.', 'With that being said, I’m considering this a “soft listing” to gauge interest and get the ball rolling meeting people who may be interested in renting the house while I’m traveling.', 'If you are genuinely interested I would be happy to offer a FaceTime or WhatsApp walkthrough and conversation regarding the home.', 'I have intentionally not included photos of the bedrooms out of consideration for my tenants privacy but photos will be made available if interested.', 'Each bedroom is approximately 9/10 ft x 10/11 ft.', 'The largest bedroom has a standard king size bed, the next largest room has a queen and the smallest a full.', 'Each room has a closet, mirror, bed, dresser, side tables etc…and I’m willing to furnish to accommodate.', 'The home is situated on a quiet culdesac with four other homes, minutes from everything in Great Barrington and a short drive from everywhere in South County.', 'Great location for leaf peeping, hiking, minutes from Butternut and Catamount, less than 2.5 hours from Boston, one hour from Albany, 50 minutes from Hudson, NY and 3ish hours from title: Gorgeous 3 bedroom, 2 bath
posting_body: ['SHOWINGS BY APPOINTMENT ONLY; MASKS REQUIRED (COVID PRECAUTION):', 'Friday 7/29: 12pm-2pm', 'Sunday 7/31: 2:30pm-6pm', 'Beautiful and recently renovated 3 bedroom, 2 bathroom apartment in Riverdale, available June 1.', 'A two-minute walk to Key Food, Walgreens, Starbucks and shopping on Johnson Avenue, five-minute walk to Riverdale Avenue shops, and a ten-minute walk to the 1 train.', "Walking in is a marble staircase and it's one flight up to the open dining room.", 'Straight ahead is the kitchen with cherry cabinets, granite countertops, and stainless steel appliances.', 'Behind the kitchen is a bedroom and the main floor bathroom.', 'Through the dining room, a large living room, with a door to a patio.', 'Off the living room is a small bedroom, and to your right are the stairs to the 700 sq ft+ master suite.', 'In the master suite is an en-suite bathroom with double vanities and a jacuzzi tub.', 'With more than 15 windows, this is an extremely sunny apartment.', 'In-unit laundry is in the basement (2 washers and 2 dryers).', 'Laundry area is shared with the live-in super.', 'Access to the backyard and grill.', 'Small gatherings that end by 10pm are allowed - simply coordinate with the other tenants.', 'Included in the rent are heat and hot water.', 'Tenant pays electric and gas (approximately $60-$250 monthly, depending on your air conditioner use).', 'Parking available, off-street, $150/month additional.', 'The apartment is pet friendly (up to 2 well-behaved pets considered), and strictly non-smoking.', 'Perfect for commute to Columbia and Upper West Side, about a 45-minute train ride to midtown.', 'Income 40x the monthly rent with good credit.', 'Guarantors accepted.', '1-year and 2-year leases offered.', 'Please email with any questions and to schedule a viewing.', 'Thanks!']
